<TITLE> Russia slams NATO for 'Cold War thinking' on Georgia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moscow,Sep 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A visit to Georgia by senior NATO officials this week was anti-Russian and showed the Cold War-style thinking inside the alliance, Russia's Foreign Ministry said in a statement on Wednesday. "Decisions taken as a result of the session confirmed that in NATO, the Cold War-era reflexes of 'them and us' are at work once again," the statement said. It said the visit showed an anti-Russian tendency because NATO officials only viewed war damage inside Georgia, and not in the breakaway region of South Ossetia
